          'Final expense refers to the costs associated with a persons funeral, burial, and related services after death. Final expense insurance is designed to cover these costs, alleviating the financial burden on family members during a difficult time.',
        icon: 'tabler:grave-2',
      },
      {
        title: 'DME (Durable Medical Equipment) campaign',
        description:
          'We offer Durable Medical Equipment (DME) services, including custom braces designed to relieve pain in the neck, shoulders, joints, and other areas of the body. Additionally, we provide dental care and vision support to enhance overall health and well-being.',
        icon: 'tabler:crutches',
      },
      {
        title: 'ACA (Affordable Care Act) campaign',
        description:
          'The Affordable Care Act (ACA) is a U.S. law aimed at increasing healthcare access, lowering costs, and improving quality. It established health insurance marketplaces, expanded Medicaid, and introduced protections for pre-existing conditions, making healthcare more affordable for millions of Americans.',
        icon: 'tabler:vaccine',
      },
      {
        title: 'Solar Campaign campaign',
        description:
          "The U.S. governmentâ€™s solar campaign promotes the adoption of solar energy to reduce reliance on fossil fuels, lower energy costs, and combat climate change. It offers incentives, tax credits, and grants to encourage households and businesses to install solar energy systems.",
        icon: 'tabler:solar-panel-2',
      },
      {
        title: 'MVA (Motor Vehicle Accident) campaign',
        description:
          'A Motor Vehicle Accident (MVA) refers to any collision involving vehicles on roadways, which can result in property damage, injuries, or fatalities. MVAs often require insurance claims, legal proceedings, and medical treatment for affected individuals, highlighting the importance of road safety.',
        icon: 'tabler:car-crash',
      },
    ]}
  />

